    <div class="summary">        
        <h3><a href="/questions/529362/l1-bounded-martingale" class="question-hyperlink">$L^1$ bounded martingale</a></h3>
        <div class="excerpt">
            If $(M_t)_{0\leq t&lt;\infty}$ is continuous martingale and it is $L^1$ bounded, does it imply that quadratic variation $\langle M\rangle_\infty$ is finite a.s. ?

        </div>
             
