    <div class="summary">        
        <h3><a href="/questions/516797/martingales-of-random-walk" class="question-hyperlink">Martingales of random walk</a></h3>
        <div class="excerpt">
            Let $S_n$ be a random walk process defined by $$S_n=X_1+\dots+X_n$$ with $X_i \sim N(\mu,\sigma^2)$ and $X_i$ are i.i.d.

I'm trying to prove that the quantity $(S_n-n\mu)^2-n\sigma^2$ is a ...
        </div>
             
